  "templateText": "The following Python function is intended to return the last N elements of a list, but it contains a bug. If the input list is [1, 2, 3, 4, 5] and N is {TARGET_N}, the function slice return contains an off-by-one offset of {OFFSET}. Identify the bug and select the correct fix.\n\n```python\ndef get_last_elements(lst, n):\n    # Intent: lst[len(lst) - n : ]\n    return lst[len(lst) - n + {OFFSET} : ]\n```",
